# Agent–user interaction (this project)

## After code changes: manual steps

When the agent has run and changed code, list any **manual steps** the user must do in a **descriptive** way: say **what** to change, **where** (e.g. Supabase Dashboard, Hostinger, GitHub, local terminal, cloud provider console), and **on which platform** so they can follow without guessing.

## How to explain what changed

Keep explanations **short** but still **descriptive**. Use plain language so someone with **little coding experience** can understand what changed and why it matters, without long technical essays.

## Clarifications: ask, do not assume

**Do not assume** missing context (environments, accounts, constraints, or intent). **Ask** instead. Phrase questions **clearly and descriptively** so the user understands what information is needed and can answer accurately.
